The paper deals with algorithms for approximating earth mover distance over metrics with bounded doubling dimension, which is a topic in computational geometry and data structures (cs.CG and cs.DS). The paper also discusses encoding schemes and sketching schemes, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves optimization problems and metric spaces, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
